When the HTML and CSS files are downloaded, the browser needs to know how to display the elements on the screen.
To do this, it allocates a rectangle or box to each element, CSS rules are applied to the boxes of the elements.
Every box is consisted of four parts: content, padding, border, margin. Going from the center to the outside.
You can use CSS rules to control the content sizes: width: 1px; min-width:1px; max-width:2px; height:1px; min-height:1px; max-height:2px;

The padding extends the content size: padding box width, padding box height. The thickness of the padding is determined by padding-top, padding-bottom, padding-left, padding-right.
Padding box width can be calculated as content width + padding left-side + padding right-side.
Padding box height can be calculated as conteng height + padding top-side + padding bottom-side.

The border goes around the padding and content. Border box width, border box height. There are different types of borders, solid border, dashed border, dotted border, double border.
Border box width can be calculated as padding width + border left-side + border right-side.
Border box height can be calculated as padding height + border top-side + border bottom-side.

The margin extends the border area to separate the element from its neighboring elements. Margin box width, margin box height.
CSS rules: margin-top:4px; margin-bottom:3px; margin-left:1px; margin-right:2px;
Margin box width can be calculated as border box width + margin left-side + margin right-side.
Margin box height can be calculated as border height + margin top-side + margin bottom-side.
